cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is about generating descriptive paragraphs for images using a combination of computer vision and natural language processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of recurrent neural networks for language modeling, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques for reasoning about language, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the use of text analysis techniques to evaluate the generated paragraphs, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
